Impact Linkage Engine — 'From Papers to Proof'
Judge Evaluation Scores
Innovation: 9.0
Feasibility: 7.5
Impact Alignment (SDGs / Research Mission): 9.0
Clarity of Storytelling: 8.5
Innovation
What’s outstanding: Elevates the dashboard from descriptive analytics to evidence-level attribution
(papers → jobs/policies/startups/clinics). Smart precision/recall mode and evidence drawer with
confidence scores signal serious thinking about trust and UX. Bridges the “last mile” from research
outputs to fundable narratives—rare and differentiating.
What to sharpen: Define causal language guardrails and show 2–3 phrasing templates that avoid
overclaiming. Add a “negative evidence” notion (why a candidate was rejected) to further strengthen
credibility.
Feasibility
What’s strong: Realistic narrow-scope MVP (1 SDG, 2–3 exemplars). Uses proven building blocks:
entity resolution + embeddings + rule features + human-in-the-loop. Clear data pathway via public
feeds (NIH/NSF, USPTO, state registries, agency PDFs).
What to mitigate: Clarify source access & rate limits. Show a ground-truthing plan (10–20
hand-validated linkages) and target Precision@k ≥ 0.85. Add a lightweight governance & data retention
note.
Impact Alignment
What’s strong: Directly advances institutional priorities: transparent, measurable societal impact
mapped to SDGs. Benefits multiple stakeholders: Leadership, Donors, Researchers.
What to deepen: Include place-based metrics for SDGs with local relevance. Add an equity lens (e.g.,
outcomes in underserved communities) to strengthen mission fit.
Clarity of Storytelling
What’s compelling: “From Papers to Proof” is memorable; the 5-minute demo storyboard is crisp and
visual. The Impact Card metaphor is intuitive, portable to slides, PDFs, and web.
What to polish: Open with one named example to humanize the story. Tighten the ask: “Pilot SDG7,
10 validated cards, Precision@5 ≥ 0.85, 2 donor briefings.”
Overall Verdict
Finalist-level concept with a credible MVP and clear institutional value. Nail precision, governance, and
one unforgettable end-to-end example, and this becomes a category-defining entry.
100-Word Vision Statement
Illinois creates world-class sustainability research, but impact remains hidden in PDFs and scattered
databases. The Impact Linkage Engine turns papers into verifiable proof: evidence-backed cards that
link research to jobs, policies, startups, and healthier communities—each with citations, confidence,
and transparent reasoning. With a precision-first pipeline and human-in-the-loop review, we make
impact measurable, trustable, and fundable. Leaders see portfolio strengths and gaps; donors see
stories they can invest in; researchers discover pathways to translation and collaboration. Starting with
one SDG, we will build an expandable, open framework that shows what Illinois research does—not
just what it publishes, for Illinois and beyond.